2026-04-16 12:38:35 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['control (ambient sensor) module relay driver / relay contacts'] hypothesis_explanation='The power-supply module is healthy (its LED is on and battery assumed good). The load module appears healthy: earlier it could illuminate, and its behavior depends only on receiving correct 12 V polarity through the series diode. The later multimeter test shows the control-module output never reaches anywhere near 12 V, staying around 0.36 V regardless of light level or timing-pot position. This indicates that the fault lies entirely within the control (ambient sensor) module.\n\nEarlier symptom (lamp off for 0.5 s every ~20 s) is consistent with the timing circuit or relay driver causing periodic dropouts. After diagnostic manipulation of the timing potentiometer, the situation worsened to a state where the relay never closes properly and only a small leakage voltage (~0.36 V) appears at the output.\n\nThus the most probable root cause is a failure inside the control module: either the relay driver circuitry or the relay contacts themselves are faulty, preventing the relay from ever supplying a solid 12 V to the load. Replacing/repairing the relay and its driver circuit within the control module should restore correct operation.'
