RESULT: The sensor-bias low node at the sensor bias resistor’s negative side is at approximately 0.119 V relative to the module’s negative input terminal. The sensor-bias low node is resistively connected (~1.3 Ω) to the control input cable (−), i.e., the module’s negative input rail.
