description: With the control module powered (load disconnected), directly measure the voltage between the module’s +12 V input terminal and the low side of the sensor bias resistor (the ≈0.12 V node) using a multimeter, then measure between that same low node and the module’s negative input terminal. Confirm whether the sensor-bias low node actually sits close to +12 V relative to the module negative, or close to 0 V; this will reveal whether the + and − supply rails are reversed in the control module’s internal circuitry or at its input connector despite earlier continuity checks., outcome='Two voltage measurements were taken at the control module and both steps completed successfully. No numeric voltage values or polarity information were reported in the outcomes, so the relative potential of the sensor-bias low node to the module’s +12 V and negative terminals is not specified.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control (ambient sensor) module supply polarity and reference node,
description: With the control module powered and load disconnected, explicitly measure and record: (1) V(+12_in to −_in), (2) V(sensor‑bias low node to −_in), and (3) V(+12_in to sensor‑bias low node), taking note of both magnitude and sign. Also confirm whether the comparator/driver reference pin is tied to the sensor‑bias low node or to the − rail. Report all three numeric voltages and the reference for each measurement., outcome='Measured V(+12_in to −_in) ≈ 11.9875 V − 0.0002 V ≈ 11.9873 V.  \nMeasured V(sensor‑bias low node to −_in) ≈ 0.119 V − 0.0002 V ≈ 0.1188 V.  \nMeasured V(+12_in to sensor‑bias low node) ≈ 11.9875 V − 0.119 V ≈ 11.8685 V. The comparator/driver reference pin connection was not reported in these steps.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=75.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control (ambient sensor) module comparator/driver reference pin node,
description: With the control module powered and the load disconnected, locate the comparator/driver IC or transistor stage inside the control module. Using the schematic as a guide, identify its reference/ground pin (or the node that sets the switching threshold). Measure the DC voltage of this pin relative to the module’s negative input terminal, and also relative to the sensor‑bias low node (the ≈0.12 V node). Report both voltages and whether this reference pin is tied to the sensor‑bias low node or to the true negative rail., outcome='The sensor-bias low node at the sensor bias resistor’s negative side is at approximately 0.119 V relative to the module’s negative input terminal. The sensor-bias low node is resistively connected (~1.3 Ω) to the control input cable (−), i.e., the module’s negative input rail.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=75.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control (ambient sensor) module sensor-bias low node vs. relay output path,
description: With the control module powered and still disconnected from the load, use a multimeter (referenced to the module’s negative input) to (1) measure the DC voltage at both relay output terminals and at both terminals of the “switched cables indicator” LED, and (2) check continuity (with power removed) between the sensor‑bias low node (~0.12 V node) and each relay output terminal / LED terminal. Determine whether the ~0.12 V sensor‑bias node is unintentionally tied into the relay output / indicator branch instead of being isolated as the comparator reference, which could clamp the control output near 0.36 V., outcome='Measured DC voltages at the control relay are 11.9873 V on the positive terminal and 0.3592 V on the negative terminal (referenced to the module’s negative input). Continuity tests show the sensor bias resistor at 10 kΩ (nominal) and the control relay contacts at 0.01 Ω (nominal), with no additional continuity information reported between the ~0.12 V sensor‑bias node and the relay output / LED branch.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=185.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control (ambient sensor) module comparator/driver output node vs. relay coil negative terminal,
description: With the control module powered and still disconnected from the load, probe the comparator/driver output node that drives the relay coil (or the transistor’s collector/emitter that connects to the relay negative terminal). Measure the DC voltage of this driver output relative to the module’s negative input while the sensor is alternately darkened and brightly illuminated. In the same conditions, directly measure the voltage across the relay coil itself (positive coil terminal to negative coil terminal). Report whether the driver output ever pulls the coil terminal close to ground (energizing the relay), whether it sits stuck near ~0.36 V, or whether the relay coil is permanently seeing only a small voltage difference., outcome='The driver output node for the relay coil negative terminal is sitting at approximately 0.36 V relative to the module’s negative input in both sensor conditions and does not pull close to ground. The relay coil is seeing a nearly full supply voltage across it (about 11.99 V from positive to negative terminal) in both measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> physical wiring / connector orientation between power, control, and load modules,
description: Visually inspect all fast‑connection terminals between the three modules and compare to the schematic: verify that the power module’s + cable is mated to the control module’s + input, the control module’s + output is mated to the load module’s + input (the side with the series diode), and likewise for all − cables. Also confirm that no extra cross‑connections exist (e.g., a control output accidentally looped back into a control input, or a module connected upside‑down/rotated 180° so that its two leads are swapped relative to the intended stack order). Note any mismatched colors, rotated connectors, or connectors joined to the wrong partner cable., outcome='All three modules’ positive cables are consistently daisy‑chained: PSU Output Cable (+) → Control Input Cable (+) → Control Output Cable (+) → Load Input Cable (+), with no extra cross‑connections observed. All three modules’ negative cables are likewise consistently daisy‑chained: PSU Output Cable (−) → Control Input Cable (−) → Control Output Cable (−) → Load Input Cable (−). No polarity inversions or rotated/mismatched connections are present in the inspected terminals.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=100.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
